en_707170_0	Measures have been taken to beef up security in Ports in line with the anti-drug campaign being implemented island wide.
en_707170_1	Minister Sagala Ratnayake has instructed the Sri Lanka Ports Authority to take necessary steps to tighten security in the Ports.
en_707170_2	Accordingly, the Ports Authority is working hand in hand with the Sri Lanka Police to ensure security at the Colombo Port.
en_707170_3	A new security plan will be implemented.
en_707170_4	Meanwhile, Sagala Ratnayake has also informed the management of the Sri Lanka Ports Authority to carry out all transactions of the Authority in accordance with the due tender and procurement procedures.
en_707170_5	He also stressed that the activities of the Authority need to be done in hundred percent transparency.
